cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks for image-based prediction of lung cancer and personalized cancer-free progression time. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves multi-task learning and the use of novel loss functions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of medical imaging data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MED (Medical Imaging) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
